<driver id="driver/bjc600">
  <name>bjc600</name>
  <url>http://www.ghostscript.com/</url>
  <thirdpartysupplied />
  <execution>
    <ghostscript />
    <prototype>gs -q -dBATCH -dPARANOIDSAFER -dQUIET -dNOPAUSE -sDEVICE=bjc600%A%Z -sOutputFile=- -</prototype>
  </execution>
  <comments>
    <en>

     Ghostscript's built-in standard driver for Canon's inkjet
     printers.&lt;p&gt;

     NOTE: Due to a &lt;a
     href=&quot;http://bugs.ghostscript.com/show_bug.cgi?id=690032&quot;&gt;bug&lt;/a&gt;
     GPL Ghostscript 8.63 crashes when using this driver with PDF
     input data. With PostScript the driver works just fine.&lt;p&gt;

     The bug is fixed in Ghostscript 8.64 and later. For Ghostscript
     8.63 (and older) there is a &lt;a
     href=&quot;http://www.openprinting.org/download/printing/ghostscript-bjc600-bjc800-patches/bjc600-bjc800-pdf.patch&quot;&gt;patch&lt;/a&gt;
     available.&lt;p&gt;

     The PPDs from this site need Ghostscript 8.64 or newer or the
     patch to work correctly with PDF input.&lt;p&gt;

   </en>
  </comments>
